included.description: Under conventional techniques, users often forget relationship between multiple windows in a browser. The implementations include displaying a first association identifier on a tab of the second window after determining the second window associated with the first window, and displaying a first association identifier on a tab of the second window. Accordingly, the user knows the relationship between these windows without reading the content of the windows.
